          "message": "fix: harden spec-tracking workflow against script injection (#1416)\n\n* fix: harden spec-tracking workflow against script injection\n\n- Move all ${{ }} expressions out of run: blocks into env: variables\n  to prevent GitHub Actions script injection (lines 21, 125)\n- Use refs/heads/ prefix for git checkout to prevent option injection\n  via attacker-controlled branch names (github.head_ref)\n- Add path traversal validation for spec file paths\n- Pin actions/checkout to commit SHA (matching claude-code-review.yml)\n- Scope down large-pr-warning permissions to least privilege\n\nAddresses Wiz Issue 6cfd82fc-1f34-4354-9f89-a7a5c418700f (HIGH):\n  - \"Workflow should not use untrusted input in scripts\"\n  - \"Workflow should not use untrusted input in a privileged context\"\n\n* fix: reduce workflow permissions to contents: read\n\nRemove the spec file rename step that required contents: write.\nSpec-to-PR association is available via git history.\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Andrew Tretyakov <42178850+0xAndoroid@users.noreply.github.com>",
